19/05/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The June 5th snap parliamentary elections will test Macedonia's readiness to join the EU, according to a delegation of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (CoE) that visited on Wednesday (May 18th).
The delegation also stressed that the vote should be conducted in a free, peaceful and democratic atmosphere.
The CoE representatives urged all parties to recognise the election results.
The vote will be monitored by 20 CoE observers.
(Alsat M, Sitel, Makfax - 18/05/11)
